 enhancing deportations, render non-deported people stuck in precarious limbo. It brings up questions of the violence endemic to border regimes, and about racism, and bureaucratic exclusion in the Nordic welfare states.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDeportationzDenmark. 0aDeportationzSweden. 0aNoncitizens. 0aPolitical violence. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Comparative Politics.2bisacsh  aDenmark.  aSweden.  acritical border studies.  adeportation.  ahumanitarianism.  aimmigration detention.  apolitical ethnography.  aracism.  astructural violence.  awelfare state.1 aLindberg, Annika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2022 eBook-Packagez978311128144540uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152616088140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526160881423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526160881/original  a978-3-11-128144-5  Manchester University Press 2022 eBook-Packageb2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles